{
  "texts": [
    "It enables farmers to improve yields by increasing productivity and operational efficiency (Sadiku et al. 2021).",
    "IoT technologies have greatly enhanced efficiency in agriculture by enabling real-time monitoring and control of various aspects of farming operations by incorporating sensors such as soil moisture sensors and temperature sensors (Cihan 2023; Pandrea et al. 2023), IoT systems provide farmers with important data on weather conditions, soil moisture levels, and crop health.",
    "This data allows for precise decision-making in pest control, irrigation, and fertilization.",
    "These systems also allow for remote monitoring and control through smartphone applications, promoting sustainable agriculture practices and resource conservation (Pandrea et al. 2023).",
    "Additionally, IoT-based smart agriculture monitoring systems integrate advanced technologies like Arduino, GSM modems, and WiFi modems to optimize cultivation environments and enable data-driven decision-making for farmers."
  ]
}